# Monday Rate Limit Awareness

## Patterns to Flag

- API calls inside unbounded loops (`while(true)`, `for` without limit) without delay or backoff
- Missing retry logic after receiving 429 (Too Many Requests) or complexity limit errors
- No delay/sleep between rapid sequential API calls
- Ignoring `reset_in_x_seconds` from complexity responses
- `create_board` or `duplicate_board` mutations called more than 40 times without rate awareness
- Bulk operations (creating many items) without batching or throttling
- Missing `complexity` field on queries that could be expensive

## What to Do

- Add exponential backoff on 429 responses: wait `reset_in_x_seconds` then retry
- Batch item creation: use a single mutation with multiple creates when possible
- Add `complexity { before after reset_in_x_seconds }` to expensive queries
- Implement a delay (minimum 100ms) between sequential API calls in loops
- Track complexity budget: 10,000,000 points per minute (varies by plan)
- For bulk operations, process in chunks (e.g., 50 items per batch) with delays
- Log complexity costs during development to identify expensive operations

## Exceptions

- Single API calls (not in loops) where rate limiting is unlikely
- MCP tool calls (the MCP server handles its own rate limiting)
- Test/development code using low-volume test data
